<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Kolin on harshcurious</title><link>http://localhost:1313/tags/kolin/</link><description>Recent content in Kolin on harshcurious</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><lastBuildDate>Tue, 11 May 2021 13:17:46 +0530</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="http://localhost:1313/tags/kolin/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Today I Learnt 12</title><link>http://localhost:1313/posts/til12/</link><pubDate>Tue, 11 May 2021 13:17:46 +0530</pubDate><guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/til12/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="learning-kotlin"&gt;Learning Kotlin&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="creating-variables"&gt;Creating variables&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Notes from: &lt;a href="https://www.programiz.com/kotlin-programming/variable-types"&gt;https://www.programiz.com/kotlin-programming/variable-types&lt;/a&gt; and&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can define variables dynamically:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-kotlin" data-lang="kotlin"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;var&lt;/span&gt; firstname = &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Harsh&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;var&lt;/span&gt; lastname = &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Kumar&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;var&lt;/span&gt; age = &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;26&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;var&lt;/span&gt; happiness = &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0.1&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can specify the type:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-kotlin" data-lang="kotlin"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;var&lt;/span&gt; firstname:String = &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Harsh&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;var&lt;/span&gt; age:Int = &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;43&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kotlin variables can be declared in two ways:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;val&lt;/code&gt;: Immutable.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;var&lt;/code&gt;: Mutable.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3 id="basic-variable-types"&gt;Basic variable types&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;(&lt;a href="https://kotlinlang.org/docs/basic-types.html"&gt;https://kotlinlang.org/docs/basic-types.html&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Numerical types: 6 built-in types&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;Byte&lt;/code&gt;: values between -128 and 127&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;Short&lt;/code&gt;: values between -32768 and 32767 (16-bit signed two&amp;rsquo;s complement integer).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;Int&lt;/code&gt;: values between $-2^{31}$ to $2^{31}-1$ (32-bit signed two&amp;rsquo;s complement integer).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;Long&lt;/code&gt;: values between $-2^{63}$ to $2^{63}-1$ (64-bit signed two&amp;rsquo;s complement integer).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;Float&lt;/code&gt;: (single-precision 32-bit floating point number)
&lt;img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/7/7b/Float_example.PNG" alt="Float Diagram"&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;Double&lt;/code&gt;: (double-precision 64-bit floating point number)
&lt;img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a9/IEEE_754_Double_Floating_Point_Format.svg/640px-IEEE_754_Double_Floating_Point_Format.svg.png" alt="Double Diagram"&gt;
&lt;table&gt;
 &lt;thead&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;th&gt;Type&lt;/th&gt;
 &lt;th&gt;Size(bits)&lt;/th&gt;
 &lt;th&gt;Significant bits&lt;/th&gt;
 &lt;th&gt;Exponent bits&lt;/th&gt;
 &lt;th&gt;Decimal digits&lt;/th&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;/thead&gt;
 &lt;tbody&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;Float&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;32&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;24&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;8&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;6-7&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;Double&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;64&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;53&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;11&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;15-16&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Operations:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>